# Auth & client portal UX

## Unified sign-in (`/login`)

- Single login screen for staff and clients: `app/login` + `LoginClient.tsx`.
- Return URL: `next` query param only; path must be validated server-side (`safeInternalRedirectPath`). Examples: `/login?next=/client`, `/login?next=/client/reports`, `/login?next=/report/view/…`.
- Legacy `/client/login` and `?redirect=` → redirect to `/login?next=…` (no duplicate client login UI).
- Post-login (`resolvePostLoginDestination`): `role === 'client'` → honour `next` when it starts with `/client` or `/report/view/`; else `/client`. Staff must **not** be sent to `/client` via `next`; use `/dashboard` or another safe internal route.
- Idle/expiry: `loginRedirectPath` in `lib/app/sessionTiming.ts` → `/login?next=<encoded path>` (not `/client/login`).
- Emails/APIs with “sign in” links for portal clients: `/login?next=/client` (or correct `next`), never `/client/login`.

## Login branding (`AuthScreenLogo`)

- Default (staff): `NBE_LOGO_2026_BG.svg`.
- Client flows: when `clientPortalBranding` is true (`next` starts with `/client` or `/report/view/`), use **`/nbe-logo.png`**; wide mark (~4rem height, capped width). Do **not** use `/logo.png` for client-branded login.

## Tone & copy

- British spelling in UI: **organisation**.
- Formal, clear, calm — external-customer appropriate.
- Client login (branded): title **Client portal**; explain org-provided email/password for reports, PDFs, inspection photography; note email/QR links may work **without** an account but access is limited to that document; staff cross-link → internal sign-in at plain `/login`.

## Client dashboard (`app/client/page.tsx`)

- Copy: approved maintenance documentation **by inspection date**; **Maintenance reports** = chronological archive; **Photo gallery** = by door and inspection. Inline links: medium indigo + light underline (not heavy bold + underline).

## Photo gallery

- Landing (`app/client/gallery/page.tsx`): *“Inspection records are organised by door and visit date. Select a folder to view inspection photos, and hover for additional site and door information.”*
- Per visit (`app/client/gallery/[doorKey]/[reportId]/page.tsx`): (1) images from this visit; (2) full size / individual download; (3) **if photos exist**: **Download ZIP** — omit ZIP mention when empty.

## `components/client/ClientPortalNavControls.tsx`

- **`ClientPortalBackLink`**: Dashboard / All doors — `ChevronLeft`, slate, hover background, no heavy permanent underline.
- **`ClientPortalOutlineNavButton`**: e.g. **Dates** — outlined + chevron.
- **`ClientPortalZipDownloadButton`**: primary dark, `Archive` icon, **Download ZIP**; only when photos exist.
